Reasoning: The paper deals with the proof-program correspondence and the transformation of proofs into programs, which are topics related to logic and computation. The use of realizability algebras and the method of forcing also suggest a connection to mathematical logic and set theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves the development of programs, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of ultrafilters and well orderings suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
